  <p>When designers need to talk about abstract concepts or convey a feeling, we often use photos or drawings to do so. These photos and drawings are called "references" because you should "reference" them when reading the text or listening to the presentation that accompanies them. In the example below, the designer wants to describe something that is sunny, and has collected the image examples to talk about what they mean when they talk about sunny.
  </p>


